    {
      "contentFieldValue": {
        "data": "<p><span style=\"color: #434343;\">We have enhanced the capabilities of the Path Analysis tool by including the visualization of Exit pages. You can now gain deeper insights into user behavior by not only visualizing the referrer pages but also tracking the exit pages. This feature empowers you to understand not just where users come from but also where they go after interacting with your pages.</span></p>\n\n<h1 id=\"h_01HGYS1WJ6JKY669A3MYS87CHW\"><span style=\"color: #434343;\">Key Benefits:</span></h1>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><span style=\"color: #434343;\">Comprehensive User Flow Analysis: Our enhanced feature provides a comprehensive view of user interactions. You can now have a more holistic view of the user journey, from their entry points (referrer pages) to their exit points (exit pages).</span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"color: #434343;\">Improved Decision-Making: With access to exit page data, you can make more informed decisions to optimize your content, user experience, and engagement strategies. Identify areas that need improvement and capitalize on successful user journeys.</span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"color: #434343;\">Enhanced User Engagement: Understanding the pages that users exit from allows you to tailor your content and calls to action to keep users engaged and reduce bounce rates.</span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<h1 id=\"h_01HGYS2415BC0EYWBPRRHSBXBJ\">How it Works</h1>\n\n<p><span style=\"color: #434343;\">To use this feature simply navigate to the Path Analysis tab for any page. From there you will be able to see the newly added visualization for Exit pages.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color: #434343;\"><img alt=\"\" data-fileentryid=\"26937402\" height=\"489\" src=\"/documents/d/customer-portal/screenshot-from-2023-12-05-21-20-41-png\" width=\"700\">&nbsp;</span></p>"
      },
